Importing Ensembl gene annotations and getting entrez ids

This step is important to make sure Ensembl ids are converted to entrez ids, using the biomaRt package, since clusterProfiler works primarily with entrez ids.

db_homo_s <- useMart(biomart = 'ENSEMBL_MART_ENSEMBL', dataset = 'hsapiens_gene_ensembl')

# Function to convert and append Entrez ID to data frames

translator <- function(df_ranked, info2cluster){
  new_df <- df_ranked
  dictionary <- getBM(attributes = c('ensembl_gene_id', 'entrezgene_id'),
                      filters = 'ensembl_gene_id', values = new_df$Gene.ID,
                      mart = db_homo_s, uniqueRows = F, useCache = T)
  
  new_df <- left_join(new_df, dictionary, by = join_by('Gene.ID' == 'ensembl_gene_id'),
                      multiple = 'first') %>% relocate(entrezgene_id, .after = Gene.ID)
  
  colnames(new_df) <- c('ensembl', 'entrez', 'metric')
  
  if (missing(info2cluster)){return(new_df)}
  
  else {
    new_df$group <- info2cluster
    
    return(new_df)}

}

hsGO <- GOSemSim::godata(OrgDb = 'org.Hs.eg.db', keytype = 'ENSEMBL', ont = 'BP')

#Example of translator function call
SCZ_tnf_vs_SCZ_ns <- translator(SCZ_tnf_vs_SCZ_ns, 'vs_SCZ_ns')

GSEA with GO terms or KEGG Pathways

The clusterProfiler package has a function that allows gene-set enrichment analysis between multiple groups at once, called compareCluster. From the results of this function, users can generate a wide range of different plots and retrieve dataframes to create summarized tables, including core-enriched genes and leading edges.

Here, we included all these steps in a single custom-made function called cluster_comparision that was used to retrieve dataframes to generate the Supplementary Tables shown in this work as well as the dotplots figures summarizing our findings.

cluster_comparison <- function(df_ranked_list, name, select_fun = c('gseGO', 'gseKEGG', 'gseDGN', 'gseDO'), reversed = FALSE){
  
  # Preparing ranked list to compare cluster function
  
  new_df <- data.frame(df_ranked_list[1])
  cluster_df <- new_df[,2:4]
  
  i <- 2
  
  while (i <= length(df_ranked_list)){
    new_df <- data.frame(df_ranked_list[i])
    new_df <- new_df[,2:4]
    
    cluster_df <- rbind(cluster_df, new_df)
    
    i <- i + 1}
  
  rm(new_df)
  
  # Indicating whether cluster results should be read as it is on in reversed order, depending on how the original dataframe was organized
  
  if (!is.logical(reversed)){
    stop('Not a logical value! Only TRUE or FALSE values are allowed!')}
  
  else{
    
    if (reversed){cluster_df$metric <- -1 * cluster_df$metric}
    
    else{}}
  
  # Choosing between GO Biological 
  
  if (select_fun == 'gseGO' | select_fun == 'gseKEGG'){
    
    if (select_fun == 'gseGO'){title_dotplot <- 'GO Biological Process'
      cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                                data = cluster_df, ont = 'BP',
                                OrgDb = 'org.Hs.eg.db',
                                minGSSize = 15, maxGSSize = 500, eps = 0,
                                pvalueCutoff = 0.05, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                                verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}
    
    else{title_dotplot <- 'KEGG Pathways'
      cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                                data = cluster_df, organism = 'hsa', 
                                keyType = 'ncbi-geneid',
                                minGSSize = 15, maxGSSize = 500, eps = 0,
                                pvalueCutoff = 0.05, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                                verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}}
  
  else{stopifnot('gseGO', 'gseKEGG')}
  
  cluster <- setReadable(cluster, OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, keyType = 'ENTREZID')
  
  cluster@compareClusterResult$Expression[cluster@compareClusterResult$NES > 0] <- 'Up'
  cluster@compareClusterResult$Expression[cluster@compareClusterResult$NES < 0] <- 'Down'
  
  # CREATE RESULTS TABLE
  
  res <- data.frame(cluster@compareClusterResult)
  
  write.table(res[,c(1,4:length(res)-1)], file = paste0('Compare_cluster_',
              title_dotplot, '_', name,'.csv'), quote = F, sep = '\t', row.names = F)
  
  # CREATE DOTPLOT
  
  cluster_plot <- cluster
  
  cluster_plot@compareClusterResult$p.adjust <- -log10(cluster_plot@compareClusterResult$p.adjust)
  
  max_p.adjust <- ceiling(max(cluster_plot@compareClusterResult$p.adjust))
  
  divisor <- floor(max_p.adjust / 4)
  
  dot_go <- dotplot(cluster_plot, x = 'Cluster', color = 'p.adjust', showCategory = 5,
                    split = 'Expression', size = 'GeneRatio', label_format = 40) +  ggtitle(title_dotplot) +
    scale_fill_viridis(name = expression(bold('-log'[10]*' (p-adj)')), option = 'H',
                       limits = c(0, max_p.adjust), breaks = seq(0, max_p.adjust, divisor)) +
    scale_size_continuous(name = 'GeneRatio', limits = c(0, 1), breaks = seq(0.1, 0.7, 0.2), range = c(1,10)) +
    theme(legend.title = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold'),
          title = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 12, hjust = 0.5),
          axis.text.x = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 10, angle = 45, hjust = 1, vjust = 1),
          axis.title.x = element_blank(),
          axis.text.y = element_text(family = 'sans', size = 8),
          axis.ticks.length = unit(8, "pt"),
          panel.border = element_rect(color = 'black', fill = NA, linewidth = 1),
          axis.line = element_line(color = 'black', linewidth = 1),
          axis.ticks = element_line(color = 'black', linewidth = 1),
          strip.background = element_rect(color = 'black', fill = 'grey80', linewidth = 1),
          strip.placement = 'outside',
          strip.text = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 10)) +
    facet_wrap(~fct_rev(Expression)) 
  
  ggsave(paste0('Compare_cluster_', title_dotplot, '_', name, '.tiff'),
         plot = dot_go, width = 200, height = 200, unit = 'mm', compression = 'lzw')
  
  # Return cluster data
  
  return(cluster)
  
}

Sorting expression of core-enriched genes by variance

To generate heatmaps displaying gene expression changes associated to each GO term or KEGG pathway, files containing logCPM (previously generated in the DEG analysis using EdgeR) were firstly opened and sorted by decreasing gene expression variance among groups.
